class expression_parser implements recursive descent parser with the following
grammar rules:

  EXPR          ::= PROD+EXPR | PROD-EXPR | PROD
  PROD          ::= TERM*PROD | TERM/PROD | TERM
  TERM          ::= -TERM | TERM FUNC | FUNC | NUM
  FUNC          ::= log(EXPR) | (EXPR)

or in pseudo-regex:
  EXPR      ::=  PROD([+\-]EXPR)*
  PROD      ::=  TERM([*\/]PROD)?
  TERM      ::=  -*(NUM|FUNC)(FUNC)*
  FUNC      ::=  (log)?\(EXPR\)
